Package ch.nolix.core.interfaces

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ApproximativeEqualing
    An approximative equaling object can be checked if it equals approximatively another object.
    Clearable<C extends Clearable<C>>
    A clearable object is an object that contains elements that can be removed.
    Closable  
    Freezable<F extends Freezable<F>>
    A freezable object can be frozen.
    IFluentObject<FO>
    A fluent object is an object that can return itself casted to its concrete type.
    Indexed
    An indexed object has an index.
    IRequestableContainer
    A requestable container is a container that: -Contains elements that can have a name.
    Namable<N extends Namable<N>>
    A namable object is a named object whose name can be set programmatically.
    Named
    A named object has a name.
    OptionalNamable<ON extends OptionalNamable<ON>>
    An optional namable object is a namable object whose name can be set and removed programmatically.
    OptionalSignable<OS extends OptionalSignable<OS>>
    An optional signable object is a signable object whose info string can be removed programmatically.
    OptionalTokenable<OT extends OptionalTokenable<OT>>
    An optional tokenable object is a tokenable object whose token can be removed programmatically.
    Refreshable
    A refreshable object can be refreshed.
    Resettable
    A resettable object can be reset.
    Runnable
    A runnable object can run something.
    Signable<S extends Signable<S>>
    A signable object is a signed object whose info string can be set programmatically.
    Signed
    A signed object has an info string.
    Tokenable<T extends Tokenable<T>>
    A tokenable object is a tokened object whose token can be set programmatically.
    Tokened
    A tokened object has a token.
    Typed
    A typed object has a type.
    TypeRequestable
    A type requestable object can return information about its type.
    Versioned
    A versioned object has a single version number.
